                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><b>Rigorre Morrtisse</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/09/2003&nbsp;: 09:25:10 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> The below quote was taken from another thread (one of recent many) regarding our apparent loss of our ability to solo.  I think my comments merit a new thread.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">I don t understand Verant Politics.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote">What about them do you not understand?  They do not want people to solo through their game ...is it not obvious yet?  They build their entire game around a 6-person group or (more recently) a multi-group raid and I will bet you dollars to do**** that it pissed them off to NO END when people figured out how to solo in PoP and it was still a more beneficial option than grouping.<br /><br />Do you people not see this?<br /><br />Is it their intent to abolish soloing altogether?  It think it would be if they could get away with it ...but they can't ...not without completely and utterly trashing their entire class system.  Anyone with the ability to heal or avoid damage plus deal some kind of damage to the enemy is able to solo.  It's impossible to get rid of.<br /><br />  So, what's the next best thing?  Make it where soloing is not worth the effort.  Make it so that it takes more mana per kill dealing with adds, pet taunt agro, and *fixed* pathing.<br /><br />Risk vs. Reward.  This entire game is based on that one very very simple theory.  I contend that SOE is raising the risk of soloing to the point that it is no longer feasible to do so.  Everything they have done in the past few MONTHS has been done to that end result.  <br /><br />THEY DO NOT WANT IT MORE BENEFICIAL TO SOLO THAN TO GROUP.<br /><br />Are they 'picking' on the necromancer class?  I don't think so.  Most of the so-called 'nerfs' in recent history have been targeted at specific abilities of other classes that Necromancers happen to share.  Maybe I'm wrong there ...if so, please feel free to correct me.<br /><br />I think, ultimately, whatever is happening to the Necromancer class is being caused by one thing ...the Necromancer class.  We have people who are PLing new frog clerics to level 65 with epic in a matter of days (I still believe that bragging about it was a bad thing ...), we have Necromancers soloing Kunark dragons, we have Necromancers and just a few other classes killing things that should normally take a raid force to kill.  You brag about this ...and then you expect for SOE to turn a blind eye and do nothing about it?  Are you daft?<br /><br />Remember, I'm a necromancer too.  I'm affected just like you are, but I can lift my head above thinking about only myself for a short instant to see where SOE is coming from.  I'm telling you ...you people need to start steeling yourselves up for the day (and it is coming) where soloing is not going to be anything resembling the xp\cash cow it once was.  Better that you realize it now.  Anyone who doesn't see it coming needs to have their head examined.<br /><br />Discuss.<br /><br /><br /><center>"You couldn't get a clue during the clue mating season in a field full of horny clues if you smeared your body with clue musk and did the clue mating dance."<br /><img src="http://www.emprisebank.com/4/res/img/12345678.jpg" border="0"><br /><font size="2"><font color="yellow"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=438887" target="_blank">Magelo Profile</a></font id="yellow"></font id="size2"><br /></center></span></font></td>
