                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Daedrea Darksoul</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/09/2003&nbsp;: 3:01:53 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> You can't analyze it.<br /><br />I own a professional development studio in real life.  I know EverQuest is more complex than any of my clients currently demand, but with a professional eye I can tell you a few things.<br /><br />1) Sony basically has no idea whats going on in its game.  Their view of the game is VERY skewed and VERY limited, be it from a few contacts on a test server, the devs play characters, or some misinformed /feedback or /bug that they take in earnest.  All the systems that make up this game are completely foreign to them much less the way they interact.<br /><br />Look at what they did to charm.  Ooh, charm is letting people get exp too fast.  Ok, chop 1/3 off that.  Ooh, charmed pets are tanking hard mobs in the planes, ok make them agro on PCs above all.  Ooh, charmed pets are a little "too reliable", ok lets take off that resist mod.  Not exactly sure what it does but I know it'll make things better!<br /><br />Now what do you have?  A completely, utterly useless spell.  Why?  Because their programmers have NO IDEA how to balance this game.<br /><br />This may seem harsh.  If Absor or someone is reading this they may say, and Absor has said, "hey, my programmers are some of the best I've ever seen!"  That may be the case.  But they don't understand what they are programming.  They are RUINING this game.<br /><br />2.)  Verant has no quality control, no programming standards, no internal do***entation, and no public relations.  No one checks anything before they push it to 400,000 people.  Their programming is constantly a case of "one hand doesn't know what the other is doing."  They have no standards, versioning, nothing.  <br /><br />And public relations is non-existant.  Their "PR Rep", Absor, seems to think there is nothing wrong with the game.  Their programmers are forced to PROGRAM because of all the broken aspects of this game.  What are we left with?  FAN FAIRES ARE OUR PRIMARY SOURCE OF GAME INFORMATION, ONCE EVERY FEW MONTHS.<br /><br />That is RIDICULOUS.<br /><br />Sony should be ashamed to associate their name with a development team like EverQuest has.  They are VERY lucky that no other company has been able to put out a game with the depth that 4 years of screw ups in EQ have accidentally brought to EQ.<br /><br />Yes, I still play this game.  Lack of anything better to play.  All my friends play this game too.  But the actual GAME, its ****.  Absolute ****.  And I can't wait till there is something better out there.  This may be my anger talking that they manage to ruin every single patch they ever have to this game.  Severely.  But it may be the truth.<br /><br />Flame on asskissers.<br /><br />Lich Daedrea Darksoul</span></font></td>
